For the last year, payday in Newark every other Friday -- has been a day for city employees to work in casual attire.

Too casual, some officials thought, citing problems with jeans that were fashionable but frayed, jeans with holes in them and tops that exposed too much skin. This week the city's business administrator, Glenn A. Grant, called a halt to the dress-down days. "Neatness and cleanliness are essential," he said in a letter to department directors. SUSAN JO KELLER